AN ACT relating to periods of observance; designating the month
of September of each year as “Perimenopause Awareness
Month” in this State; designating the month of October of
each year as “Menopause Awareness Month” in this
State; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, certain days, weeks and months of observance are
2 recognized in this State. (NRS 236.018-236.095) Sections 2 and 3 of this bill,
3 respectively, designate: (1) the month of September of each year as
4 “Perimenopause Awareness Month”; and (2) the month of October of each year as
5 “Menopause Awareness Month” in the State of Nevada. Additionally, sections 2
6 and 3 require the Governor to issue annually a proclamation encouraging the
7 observance of these months.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 236 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. The month of September of each year is
4 designated as “Perimenopause Awareness Month” in this State.
5 2. The Governor shall issue annually a proclamation
6 encouraging the observance of Perimenopause Awareness Month.
7 The proclamation must, without limitation, call upon news media,
